Om karasana is the last posture of the fourth series of Ashtanga Yoga. It represents the sacred sound Om, as Pranava, the universal root sound of innate divinity contained within all life. In order to try this posture you need both strength and flexibility in your hips. Energetically it represents a connection Into the subtle body and builds an inward focus of the mind. Being the last posture of the fourth series makes it even harder than it you try it outside of the sequence. Just as the sound Om symbolizes the divine each posture symbolizes a deep connection with yourself. Respect the practice by commuting yourself to it every day. Filmed by @elena_pinto @samahitaretreat
